Name: endodermal sinus tumor
Definition: A germ cell cancer that has_material_basis_in cells that line the yolk sac of the embryo.

Name: obsolete metastasis to vagina
Definition: A germ cell cancer that has_material_basis_in cells that line the yolk sac of the embryo.

Name: obsolete alternating exotropia with A pattern
Definition: A germ cell cancer that has_material_basis_in cells that line the yolk sac of the embryo.

Name: brain germinoma
Definition: A brain cancer that is characterized by abnormally proliferating cells

Name: obsolete intracranial germinoma
Definition: A brain cancer that is characterized by abnormally proliferating cells

Name: germ cell and embryonal cancer
Definition: A germ cell cancer that is derives_from a mixture of germs cells and embryonal cells.

Name: germinoma
Definition: A germ cell cancer that lacks histologic differentiation. It usually refers to a tumor in the brain.

Name: mixed germ cell cancer
Definition: A germ cell cancer that occurs in many forms.

Name: seminoma
Definition: A germinoma that has_material_basis_in cells that make sperm and eggs.

Name: dysgerminoma
Definition: A germ cell cancer that derives_from cells that give rise to egg cells.

Name: extragonadal germ cell cancer
Definition: A germ cell cancer that derives_from germ cells that are found in areas of the body other than the ovary or testicle. The tumors originate in the sperm forming cells in the testicles or egg producing cells in the ovary.

Name: fallopian tube germ cell cancer
Definition: A fallopian tube cancer that derives_from germ cells.

Name: pediatric germ cell cancer
Definition: A germ cell cancer that presents in childhood.

Name: embryonal cancer
Definition: A germ cell cancer that is associated with an embryo.
